survey_response.review_text: I have been with Dr. Shilpa from the start of my pregnancy. My entire pregnancy journey including delivery was a very smooth experience thanks to Dr. Shilpa's expertise and timely advice in terms of medication, regular tests and check ups. Due to Dr. Shilpa's positive & calm personality as well as assertive nature, we never panicked or felt nervous at any stage during the pregnancy. I would highly recommend Dr. Shilpa to anyone for a smooth pregnancy as her priority is patient comfort and also for her extensive experience. Thank you Dr. Shilpa for your support and guidance in the past year.

Dr Shilpa Abhyankar came highly recommended from my family physician for my first preganancy. The preganancy itself was challenging as I had to be on complete bed rest for 9 months. Dr Shilpa has been a firm, asseritive and strong guide through this journey. She has been extremely involved and  meticulous with respect to scans and ensuring that me and the baby were safe. I  had an  episode of bleeding for which she was present even at 4 am. She made arrangements for premature delivery and NICU if need be. Close to my due date I found the fetal movements to be lesser. She was prompt in asking me to do a scan and planned for an emergency c section and which was the best decision! Even post the delivery she was involved and concerned about the baby as well as my health. The post natal checksups and guidance were very helpful.
All in all, I could not have asked for a more knowledgeable, meticulous and concerned gynecologist for my first preganancy.

I had been under Dr. Shilpa's treatment from the very beginning of my pregnancy and I delivered my baby at Parchure Nursing home. Her judgements were always very accurate which helped us in making the right decisions at right time. The staff of Parchure Nursing home is well trained and very helping. The atmosphere was very homely and comforting, following all the necessary precautions, especially in the view of Covid. I would recommend her not only for her expertise but also for the genuine concern and care that she has for her patients.
